      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is the key.\n\nnstack_slots is always the number of stack slots we have in this call to jit().\n\nWe start it at one-per-instruction, then *stack_hint goes from -1 up to the maximum number of stack slots used during the call (the scalar and vector values might be different), and then the second time around that *stack_hint will be the new nstack_slots.\n\nSo e.g. we could see these four states at the point where *stack_hint updates when jitting one program\n\n1st jit, vector: nstack_slots \u003d 2032, *stack_hint\u003d-1, next_stack_slot\u003d22  --\u003e *stack_hint\u003d22\n1st jit, scalar: nstack_slots \u003d 2032, *stack_hint\u003d22, next_stack_slot\u003d23  --\u003e *stack_hint\u003d23\n2nd jit, vector: nstack_slots \u003d 23  , *stack_hint\u003d23, next_stack_slot\u003d22\n2nd jit, vector: nstack_slots \u003d 23  , *stack_hint\u003d23, next_stack_slot\u003d23",
